# RvsB v4.0: Vibrant & Interactive Platform

Building the "Pro" version of the platform with high-end aesthetics, a user-defined network builder, and active human-in-the-loop guidance for AI agents.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **UI Transformation**: Moving from a "utilitarian" theme to a highly vibrant, motion-heavy "premium" theme (Cyberpunk/Glassmorphism style).
> **Network Customization**: This requires refactoring the backend environment to support dynamic node definitions instead of hardcoded services.

## Proposed Changes

---

### [Component] UI/UX & Design System
Summary: Elevate the dashboard from functional to "Wow".

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///d:/College/RvsB/ui/src/index.css)
- Implement a radical color palette: Deep Obsidian, Neon Cyber-Red, Electric Blue.
- Add Glassmorphism utility classes.
- Define `@keyframes` for "Scanning" and "Glitch" effects on critical UI elements.

#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///d:/College/RvsB/ui/src/App.jsx)
- Integrate **Framer Motion** for all page transitions and card reveals.
- Redesign the sidebar with icon-only and expanded states.
- Implement a "Command Console" overlay for real-time user-to-AI prompting.

---

### [Component] Interactive Network Map & Builder
Summary: Transform the static map into a playable, draggable, and buildable canvas.

#### [NEW] [MapBuilder.jsx](file:///d:/College/RvsB/ui/src/components/MapBuilder.jsx)
- A new sub-page allowing users to drag "Service Pills" (SSH, HTTP, etc.) onto a target network map.
- Export as JSON configuration for the environment.

#### [MODIFY] [NetworkMap.jsx](file:///d:/College/RvsB/ui/src/components/NetworkMap.jsx)
- Switch to **ReactFlow** or **D3-force** for physics-based layout.
- Click a node to see detailed logs/stats for that specific service.
- Double-click to manual-patch (human intervention).

---

### [Component] Backend & Agent Refactor
Summary: Support dynamic environments and human guidance.

#### [MODIFY] [environment.py](file:///d:/College/RvsB/src/envs/rvsb_env/server/environment.py)
- Refactor [RvsBEnvironment](file:///d:/College/RvsB/src/envs/rvsb_env/server/environment.py#28-221) to accept a `config` object in `.reset()`.
- Dynamically instantiate services based on the user-defined map.

#### [MODIFY] [reasoning_layer.py](file:///d:/College/RvsB/agents/llm/reasoning_layer.py)
- Update the prompt template to include `user_guidance` ("Master Directive").
- Agents will prioritize tasks mentioned by the user in this field.

#### [MODIFY] [dashboard_api.py](file:///d:/College/RvsB/api/dashboard_api.py)
- Add endpoints to save/load user-defined network templates to SQLite.

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `pytest envs/test_dynamic_env.py`: Verify that the environment correctly spawns nodes from a JSON config.
- `npm run test:ui`: Verify component rendering for the new Map Builder.

### Manual Verification
1. Start [start.py](file:///d:/College/RvsB/start.py) → Open `/design`.
2. Delete two service nodes, add a custom "SCADA" node.
3. Start a match and verify the AI tries to attack the new "SCADA" node.
4. Type a prompt like "Ignore HTTP, go for SSH" and see if the AI's reasoning reflects this choice.
